id: pm-9x6e
title: "Capstone: zero the SDK import-boundary baseline (91 entries) — flip remaining CLI/MCP private-core imports to SDK primitives and harden the ratchet into a hard boundary gate"
description: "pm-8778 shipped the ratchet gate; scripts/release/sdk-import-boundary-baseline.json currently allows 91 private src/core imports from src/cli + src/mcp. Each SDK promotion item (pm-rjqr/98cz/zwpp/je50/4a7m/3mna/oxrw/oslr) flips its own domain's CLI handlers, but no child owns the terminal state: (1) residual imports not covered by any single domain promotion, (2) the MCP-layer flip — promotion ACs name CLI handlers only while the epic AC requires src/mcp to shrink to SDK-only too, (3) emptying + deleting the baseline file, (4) flipping static-quality-gate from ratchet mode to unconditional hard-deny so the boundary can never regress. Duplicate check 2026-07-06: pm-8778 (closed) built the gate mechanism; the 8 promotion items shrink the baseline domain-by-domain; searched 'boundary ratchet zero sdk-only imports capstone' — no existing item owns baseline-to-zero + gate hardening."
type: Task
status: open
priority: 2
